obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32078)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32078&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "approved bank" means the State Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the State Bank`
  line `of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), or a subsidiary bank constituted under section 3 of the State`
  line `Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959), or a corresponding new bank`
  line `constituted under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings)`
  line `Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), or a Regional Rural Bank established under section 3 of the Regional Rural Banks Act, 1976 (21 of 1976), or a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the`
  line `Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980 (40 of 1980), or a banking`
  line `company as defined under clause (e) of section 5 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949),`
  line `or a banking institution notified by the Central Government under section 51 of that Act or such other`
  line `banking institution as the State Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, approve for`
  line `the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "chit" means a transaction whether called chit, chit fund, chitty, kuri ^1[, fraternity fund,`
  line `Rotating Savings and Credit Institution] or by any other name by or under which a person enters into`
  line `an agreement with a specified number of persons that every one of them shall subscribe a certain sum`
  line `of money (or a certain quantity of grain instead) by way of periodical instalments over a definite`
  line `period and that each such subscriber shall, in his turn, as determined by lot or by auction of by tender`
  line `or in such other manner as may be specified in the chit agreement, be entitled to the ^2[net chit`
  line amount].
  line
  line `Explanation.-- A transaction is not a chit within the meaning of this clause, if in such`
  line transaction,--
  line
  line `(i) some alone, but not all, of the subscribers get the ^2[ net chit amount] without any liability to pay`
  line `future subscriptions; or`
  line
  line `(ii) all the subscribers get the ^3[gross chit amount] by turns with a liability to pay future subscriptions;`
  line
  line `(c) "chit agreement" means the document containing the articles of agreement between the`
  line `foreman and the subscribers relating to the chit;`
  line
  line ^4*****
  line
  line `(e) "chit business" means the business of conducting a chit;`
  line
  line `(f) "defaulting subscriber" means a subscriber who has defaulted in the payment of subscriptions`
  line `due in accordance with the terms of the chit agreement;`
  line
  line `(g) "discount" means the sum of money or the quantity of grain which a prized subscriber is,`
  line `under the terms of the chit agreement, required to forego and which is set apart under the said`
  line `agreement to meet the expenses of running the chit or for distribution among the subscribers or for`
  line both;
  line
  line ^5*****
  line
  line `(i) "draw" means the manner specified in the chit agreement for the purpose of ascertaining the`
  line `prized subscriber at any instalment of the chit;`
  line
  line `(j) "foreman" means the person who under the chit agreement is responsible for the conduct of`
  line `the chit and includes any person discharging the functions of the foreman under section 39;`
  line
  line `^6[(ja) "gross chit amount" means the sum-total of the subscriptions payable by all the subscribers`
  line `for any installment of a chit without any deduction of discount or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(jb) "net chit amount" means the difference between the gross chit amount and the discount, and`
  line `in the case of a fraction of a ticket means the difference between the gross chit amount and the`
  line `discount proportionate to the fraction of the ticket, and when the net chit amount is payable otherwise`
  line `than in cash, the value of the net chit amount shall be the value at the time when it becomes payable;]`
  line
  line `(k) "non-prized subscriber" does not include a defaulting subscriber;`
  line
  line `(l) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line ^7*****;
  line
  line `(n) "prized subscriber" means a subscriber who has either received or is entitled to receive the`
  line `^2[net chit amount];`
  line
  line `(o) "Registrar" means the Registrar of Chits appointed under section 61, and includes an`
  line `Additional, a Joint, Deputy or an Assistant Registrar appointed under that section;`
  line
  line `(p) "Reserve Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `^8[(pa) “share of discount” means the share of the subscriber in the amount of discount available`
  line `under the chit agreement for rateable distribution among the subscribers at each instalment of the`
  line chit.]
  line
  line `(q) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the administrator of that Union`
  line `territory appointed by the President under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(r) "subscriber" includes a person who holds a fraction of a ticket and also a transferee of a ticket`
  line `or fraction thereof by assignment in writing or by operation of law;`
  line
  line `(s) "ticket" means the share of a subscriber in a chit.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "prize amount" (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "chit amount" (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `4. Clause (d) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `5. Clause (h) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `7. Clause (m) omitted by Act 41 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `8. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32079)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Act to override other laws, memorandum, articles, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32079&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided`
  line `in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained`
  line `in any other law for the time being in force or in the memorandum or articles of association or`
  line `bye-laws or in any agreement or resolution whether the same be registered, executed or passed, as the`
  line `case may be, before or after the commencement of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) any provision contained in the memorandum, articles, bye-laws, agreement or resolution`
  line `aforesaid, shall, to the extent to which it is repugnant to the provisions of this Act, become or be void,`
  line `as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32080)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Prohibition of chits not sanctioned or registered under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32080&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) No chit shall be`
  line `commenced or conducted without obtaining the previous sanction of the State Government within whose`
  line `jurisdiction the chit is to be commenced or conducted or of such officer as may be empowered by that`
  line `Government in this behalf, and unless the chit is registered in that State in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a sanction obtained under this sub-section shall lapse if the chit is not registered within`
  line `twelve months from the date of such sanction or within such further period or periods not exceeding six`
  line `months in the aggregate as the State Government may, on application made to it in this behalf, allow.`
  line
  line `(2) An application for the purpose of obtaining a sanction under sub-section (1) shall be made by the`
  line `foreman in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The previous sanction referred to in sub-section (1) may be refused, if the foreman,--`
  line
  line `(a) had been convicted of any offence under this Act or under any other Act regulating chit`
  line `business and sentenced to imprisonment for any such offence; or`
  line
  line `(b) had defaulted in the payment of fees or the filing of any statement or record required to be`
  line `paid or filed under this Act or had violated any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(c) had been convicted of any offence involving moral turpitude and sentenced to imprisonment`
  line `for any such offence unless a period of five years has elapsed since his release:`
  line
  line `Provided that before refusing any such sanction, the foreman shall be given a reasonable opportunity`
  line `of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) The order of the State Government, and, subject to the provisions of sub-section (5), the order of`
  line `the officer empowered under sub-section (1), issuing or refusing previous sanction under this section shall`
  line `be final.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person aggrieved by the refusal to issue previous sanction by an officer empowered under`
  line `sub-section (1) may appeal to the State Government within thirty days of the date of communication to`
  line `him of such refusal and the decision of that Government on such appeal shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32081)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Prohibition of invitation for subscriptions except under certain conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32081&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `No person shall`
  line `issue or cause to be issued any notice, circular, prospectus, proposal or other document inviting the public`
  line `to subscribe for tickets in any chit unless such notice, circular, prospectus, proposal or document contains`
  line `a statement that the previous sanction required under section 4 has been obtained and the particulars of`
  line `such sanction.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32082)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Form of chit agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32082&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every chit agreement shall be in duplicate and shall be signed by`
  line `each of the subscribers or by any person authorised by him in writing and the foreman and attested by at`
  line `least two witnesses and it shall contain the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) full name and residential address of every subscriber;`
  line
  line `(b) the number of tickets including the fraction of a ticket held by each subscriber;`
  line
  line `(c) the number of instalments, the amount payable for each ticket at every instalment and the`
  line `interest or penalty, if any, payable on any default in the payment of such instalments;`
  line
  line `(d) the probable date of commencement and the duration of the chit;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of ascertaining the prized subscriber at each instalment;`
  line
  line `(f) the maximum amount of discount which the prized subscriber has to forego at any instalment;`
  line
  line `(g) the mode and proportion in which the discount is distributable by way of ^1[share of discount], foreman’s commission or remuneration of expenses for running the chit, as the case may be;;`
  line
  line `(h) the date, time and place at which the chit is to be drawn;`
  line
  line `(i) the instalment at which the foreman is to get the ^2[gross chit amount];;`
  line
  line `(j) the name of the approved bank in which chit moneys shall be deposited by the foreman under`
  line `the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) where the foreman is an individual, the manner in which a chit shall be continued when such`
  line `individual dies or becomes of unsound mind or is otherwise incapacitated;`
  line
  line `(l) the consequences to which a non-prized or prized subscriber or the foreman shall be liable in`
  line `case of violation of any of the provisions of the chit agreement;`
  line
  line `(m) the conditions under which a subscriber shall be treated as a defaulting subscriber;`
  line
  line `(n) the nature and particulars of the security to be offered by the foreman;`
  line
  line `(o) the dates on which and time during which the foreman shall, subject to the provisions`
  line `contained in section 44, allow inspection of chit records to non-prized and unpaid prized subscribers;`
  line
  line `(p) the names of the nominees of each subscriber, that is to say, the names of the persons to`
  line `whom the benefits accruing to the subscriber under the chit may be paid in the case of the death of the`
  line `subscriber or when he is otherwise incapable of making an agreement;`
  line
  line `(q) any other particulars that may, from time to time, be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, it shall be sufficient if the signature of each`
  line `subscriber is obtained in separate copies of the agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) The duration of a chit shall not extend beyond a period of five years from the date of its`
  line `commencement:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may permit the duration of a chit up to a period of ten years if it`
  line `is satisfied that it is necessary so to do, having regard to,--`
  line
  line `(a) the financial condition of the foreman;`
  line
  line `(b) his methods of operation;`
  line
  line `(c) the interests of prospective subscribers;`
  line
  line `(d) the requirements as to security; and`
  line
  line `(e) such other factors as the circumstances of the case may require.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount of discount referred to in clause (f) of sub-section (1) shall not exceed ^3[ thirty per cent.] of the ^2[gross chit amount].`
  line
  line `(4) Where the prized subscriber at any instalment of the chit is required to be determined by auction`
  line `and more than one person offer the maximum discount, the prized subscriber shall be determined by lot.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41of 2019, s. 3, for “dividend” (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “chit amount” (w.e.f. 1-1-2020)..`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2001, s. 2, for "forty per cent." (w.e.f. 01-10-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (32083)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Filing of chit agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32083&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every chit agreement shall be filed in duplicate by the foreman`
  line `with the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall retain one copy of the chit agreement and return the duplicate to the foreman`
  line `with an endorsement that the chit agreement has been registered:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Registrar may refuse to register the chit agreement on any one or more of the`
  line `following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the security offered by the foreman under section 20 is insufficient;`
  line
  line `(b) that the foreman had been convicted of any offence under this Act or under any other Act`
  line `regulating chit business and sentenced to imprisonment for any such offence;`
  line
  line `(c) that the foreman had defaulted in the payment of fees or the filing of any statement or record`
  line `required to be paid or filed under this Act or had violated any of the provisions of this Act or the rules`
  line `made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(d) that the foreman had been convicted of any offence involving moral turpitude and sentenced`
  line `to imprisonment for any such offence unless a period of five years has elapsed since his release:`
  line
  line `Provided further that before refusing to register a chit under the first proviso, the foreman shall be`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) Every endorsement made under sub-section (2) shall be conclusive evidence that the chit is duly`
  line `registered under this Act and the registration of a chit shall lapse if the declaration by the foreman under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 9 is not filed within three months from the date of such endorsement or within`
  line `such further period or periods not exceeding three months in the aggregate as the Registrar may, on`
  line `application made to him in this behalf, allow.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (32084)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Minimum capital requirements for the commencement, etc., of a chit, and creation of a reserve fund, by a company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 3, for “dividend” (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32084&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), but subject to the provisions of this Act, a company shall not commence or carry`
  line `on chit business unless it has a paid-up capital of not less than rupees one lakh.`
  line
  line `(2) Every company having a paid-up capital of less than rupees one lakh and carrying on chit business`
  line `on the commencement of this Act, shall, before the expiry of a period of three years from such`
  line `commencement, increase its paid-up capital of not less than rupees one lakh:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, if it considers it necessary in the public interest or for`
  line `avoiding any hardship, extend the said period of three years in respect of any company by such further`
  line `period or periods not exceeding two years in the aggregate:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such company shall commence any new chit the duration of which would`
  line `extend beyond the said period of three years or such extended period or periods under the first proviso`
  line `unless it increases its paid-up capital to not less than rupees one lakh.`
  line
  line `(3) Every company carrying on chit business shall create and maintain a reserve fund and shall, out of`
  line `the balance of profit of each year as disclosed in its profit and loss account and before any ^1[share of`
  line `discount] on its`
  line `shares is declared, transfer to such reserve fund, a sum equal to not less than ten per cent. of such profit.`
  line
  line `(4) No company shall appropriate any sum or sums from the reserve fund except with the prior`
  line `approval of the Registrar and, for the purpose of obtaining such approval, it shall make an application in`
  line `the prescribed form to the Registrar explaining the circumstances relating to such appropriation.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (32085)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Commencement of chit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “chit amount” (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32085&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every foreman shall, after all the tickets specified in the chit`
  line `agreement are fully subscribed, file a declaration to that effect with the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after a declaration is filed under sub-section (1), the Registrar shall, after`
  line `satisfying himself that all the requirements relating to sanction, registration of chit and other matters have`
  line `been duly complied with, grant a certificate of commencement to the foreman.`
  line
  line `(3) No foreman shall commence any auction or the draw of any chit or appropriate any ^1[gross chit amount]`
  line `unless a certificate of commencement referred to in sub-section (2) is obtained by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (32086)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Copies of chit agreement to be given to subscribers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32086&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) A foreman shall, as soon as may be`
  line `after he has obtained the certificate of commencement under sub-section (2) of section 9, but not later`
  line `than the date of the first draw of the chit, furnish to every subscriber, a copy of the chit agreement`
  line `certified to be a true copy.`
  line
  line `(2) A foreman shall, within fifteen days after the close of the month in which the draw for the first`
  line `instalment of the chit is held, file with the Registrar, a certificate to the effect that the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) have been complied with.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (32087)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Use of words "chit", "chit fund", "chitty", "kuri", "fraternity fund", or "Rotating Savings and Credit Institution".`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for section 11 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32087&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) No person shall carry on chit business unless he uses as part of his name`
  line `any of the words "chit", "chit fund", "chitty", "kuri", "fraternity fund" or "Rotating Savings and Credit`
  line `Institution" and no person other than a person carrying on chit business shall use as part of his name any`
  line `such word.br`
  line
  line `(2) Where at the commencement of this Act,—br`
  line
  line `(a) any person is carrying on chit business without using as part of his name any of the words`
  line `specified in sub-section (1); orbr`
  line
  line `(b) any person not carrying on chit business is using any such word as part of his name,`
  line `he shall, within a period of one year from such commencement, add as part of his name any such word or,`
  line `as the case may be, delete such word from his name:br`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, if it considers necessary in the public interest or for`
  line `avoiding any hardship, extend the said period of one year by such further period or periods not exceeding`
  line `one year in the aggregate.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (32088)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Prohibition of transacting business other than chit business by a company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32088&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except with`
  line `the general or special permission of the State Government, no company carrying on chit business shall`
  line `conduct any other business.`
  line
  line `(2) Where at the commencement of this Act, any company is carrying on any business in addition to`
  line `chit business, it shall wind up such other business before the expiry of a period of three years from such`
  line `commencement:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, if it considers it necessary in the public interest or for`
  line `avoiding any hardship, extend the said period of three years by such further period or periods not`
  line `exceeding two years in the aggregate.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (32089)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Aggregate amount of chits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32089&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) No foreman, other than a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals or a company or co-operative society, shall commence or conduct chits, the aggregate ^1[gross chit amount] of which at any time exceeds ^2[rupees three lakh].`
  line
  line `(2) Where the foreman is a firm or other association of individuals, the aggregate ^1[gross chit amount] of the`
  line `chits conducted by the firm or other association shall not at any time exceed,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the number of partners of the firm or the individuals constituting the association is not`
  line `less than four, a sum of rupees ^3[rupees eighteen lakhs];`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, a sum calculated on the basis of ^2[rupees three lakh] with respect`
  line `to each such partner or individual.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the foreman is a company or co-operative society, the aggregate ^1[gross chit amount] of the chits`
  line `conducted by it shall not at any time exceed ten times the net owned funds of the company or the`
  line `co-operative society, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, "net owned funds" shall mean the aggregate of`
  line `the paid-up capital and free reserves as disclosed in the last audited balance sheet of the company or cooperative society, as reduced by the amount of accumulated balance of loss, deferred revenue,`
  line `expenditure and other intangible assets, if any, as disclosed in the said balance-sheet.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 3, for "chit amount" (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., "rupees one lakh" (w.e.f. 01-10-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for, "rupees six lakhs" (w.e.f. 01-01-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (32090)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Utilisation of funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32090&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person carrying on chit business shall utilise the moneys collected`
  line `in respect of such business (other than commission or remuneration payable to such person or interest or`
  line `penalty, if any, received from a defaulting subscriber), except for--`
  line
  line `(a) carrying on chit business; or`
  line
  line `(b) giving loans and advances to non-prized subscribers on the security of subscriptions paid by`
  line `them; or`
  line
  line `(c) investing in trustee securities within the meaning of section 20 of the Indian Trusts`
  line `Act, 1882 (2 of 1882); or`
  line
  line `(d) making deposits with approved banks mentioned in the chit agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person carrying on chit business has utilised the moneys collected in respect of such`
  line `business before the commencement of this Act, otherwise than for the purposes specified in`
  line `sub-section (1), he shall secure that so much of such moneys as have not been realised before such`
  line `commencement are realised before the expiry of a period of three years from such commencement:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, if it considers it necessary in the public interest or for`
  line `avoiding any hardship, extend the said period of three years by such further period or periods not`
  line `exceeding one year in the aggregate.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (32091)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Alteration of chit agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32091&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `A chit agreement shall not be altered, added to or cancelled`
  line `except with the consent in writing of the foreman and all the subscribers to the chit.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (32092)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Date, time and place of conducting chits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32092&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every draw in a chit shall be held on the date, at`
  line `the time and place mentioned in the chit agreement and a notice therefor in such form and in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed shall be issued by the foreman to all the subscribers ^1[present in person or through video conferencing duly`
  line `recorded by the foreman.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every such draw shall be conducted in accordance with the provisions of the chit agreement and`
  line `in the presence of not less than two subscribers.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any draw was not conducted on the ground that two subscribers required to be present at a`
  line `draw under sub-section (2) were not present or on any other ground, the Registrar may, on his own`
  line `motion or on an application made by the foreman or any of the subscribers, direct that the draw shall be`
  line `conducted in his presence or in the presence of any person deputed by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (32093)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Minutes of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32093&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The minutes of the proceedings of every draw shall be prepared`
  line `and entered in a book to be kept for that purpose immediately after the closure of the draw and shall be`
  line `signed by the foreman, the prized subscribers, if present, or their authorised agents, and at least two other`
  line `subscribers who are present ^1[in person or through video conferencing], and where a direction has been made under sub-section (3) of section 16,`
  line `also by the Registrar or the person deputed by him under that sub-section.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that where two subscribers required to be present under sub-section (2) of section 16 are`
  line `present through video conferencing, the foreman shall have the minutes of the proceedings signed by such`
  line `subscribers within a period of two days of the date of the draw.]`
  line
  line `(2) The minutes referred to in sub-section (1) shall state clearly--`
  line
  line `(a) the date and hour when proceedings began and ended and the place where the draw was held;`
  line
  line `(b) the number of the instalment of the chit to which the proceedings relate;`
  line
  line `(c) the names of the subscribers present;`
  line
  line `(d) the person or persons who become entitled to the ^2[net chit amount] in the instalment;`
  line
  line `(e) the amount of discount;`
  line
  line `(f) full particulars regarding the disposal of the unpaid ^2[net chit amount], if any, in respect of any`
  line `previous instalment; and`
  line
  line `(g) any other particulars that may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 7 ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, for "prize amount" (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (32094)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Copies of minutes to be filed with Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32094&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `A true copy of the minutes of the proceedings of`
  line `every draw certified as such by the foreman shall be filed by the foreman with the Registrar within`
  line `twenty-one days from the date of the draw to which it relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (32095)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Restriction on opening of new place of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32095&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person carrying on chit business shall`
  line `open a new place of business without obtaining the prior approval of the Registrar within whose territorial`
  line `jurisdiction his registered office or, as the case may be, the place or the principal place of business is`
  line situated.
  line
  line `(2) Before granting approval under sub-section (1), the Registrar shall consult the Registrar of the`
  line `State within whose territorial jurisdiction the new place of business is proposed to be opened and shall`
  line `also keep in view the financial condition and methods of operation of the foreman, the extent to which`
  line `public interest will be served by the opening of the new place of business and such other matters as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person carrying on chit business opens a new place of business in a State other than the`
  line `State (hereinafter referred to as the State of origin) in which his registered office or the place or the`
  line `principal place of his business is situated, the Registrar of the State in which such new place of business is`
  line `opened may also exercise and perform any of the powers and functions which the Registrar of the State of`
  line `origin may exercise and perform in respect of the chit business carried on at such new place of business.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this section, "place of business" shall include any branch office, sub-office, or`
  line `any place of business where the chit business may be conducted by such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (32096)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Security to be given by foreman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32096&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the proper conduct of the chit, every foreman shall,`
  line `before applying for a previous sanction under section 4,`
  line
  line `^1[(a) deposit in the name of the Registrar, an amount equal to,--`
  line
  line `(i) fifty per cent. of the ^2[gross chit amount] in cash in an approved bank; and`
  line
  line `(ii) fifty per cent. of the ^2[gross chit amount] in the form of bank guarantee from an approved`
  line `bank; or]`
  line
  line `(b) transfer Government securities of the face value or market value (whichever is less) of not less`
  line `than one and a half times the ^2[gross chit amount] in favour of the Registrar; or`
  line
  line `(c) transfer in favour of the Registrar such other securities, being securities in which a trustee may`
  line `invest money under section 20 of the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882), of such value, as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the value of the securities referred to in clause (c) shall not, in any case, be less than`
  line `one and a half times the value of the ^2[gross chit amount] .`
  line
  line `(2) Where a foreman conducts more than one chit, he shall furnish security in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (1) in respect of each chit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar may, at any time during the currency of the chit, permit the substitution of the`
  line `security:`
  line
  line `Provided that the face value or market value (whichever is less) of the substituted security shall not be`
  line `less than the value of the security given by the foreman under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The security given by the foreman under sub-section (1), or any security substituted under`
  line `sub-section (3), shall not be liable to be attached in execution of a decree or otherwise until the chit is`
  line `terminated and the claims of all the subscribers are fully satisfied.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the chit is terminated and the Registrar has satisfied himself that the claims of all the`
  line `subscribers have been fully satisfied, he shall order the release of the security furnished by the foreman`
  line `under sub-section (1), or the security substituted under sub-section (3), as the case may be, and in doing`
  line `so, he shall follow such procedure as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `the security furnished under this section shall not be dealt with by the foreman during the currency of the`
  line `chit to which it relates and any dealing by the foreman with respect thereto by way of transfer or other`
  line `encumbrances shall be null and void.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs.by Act 10 of 2001, s. 4, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 01-10-2001).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 3, for chit amount (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (32097)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Rights of foreman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32097&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The foreman shall be entitled,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the absence of any provision in the chit agreement to the contrary, to obtain the ^1[gross chit`
  line amount]
  line `at the first instalment without deduction of the discount specified in the chit agreement, subject to the`
  line `condition that he shall subscribe to a ticket in the chit:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a case where the foreman has subscribed to more than one ticket, he shall not be`
  line `eligible to obtain more than one chit amount in a ^1[gross chit amount] discount;`
  line
  line `(b) to such amount not exceeding ^2[seven per cent.] of the ^1[gross chit amount] as may be fixed in the chit`
  line `agreement, by way of commission, remuneration or for meeting the expenses of running the chit;`
  line
  line `(c) to interest and penalty, if any, payable on any default in the payment of instalments and to`
  line `such other amounts as may be payable to him under the provisions of the chit agreement;`
  line
  line `(d) to receive and realise all subscriptions from the subscribers and to distribute the prize amounts`
  line `to the prized subscribers;`
  line
  line `(e) to demand sufficient security from any prized subscriber for the due payment of future`
  line `subscriptions payable by him.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- A security shall be deemed to be sufficient for the purposes of this clause if its`
  line `value exceeds by one-third, or of it consists of immovable properties, the value of which exceeds by`
  line `one-half, of the amount due from the prized subscriber;`
  line
  line `(f) to substitute subscribers in place of defaulting subscribers; ^3***`
  line
  line `^4[(fa) to exercise his right to lien against the credit balance in other non-prized chits; and]`
  line
  line `(g) to do all other acts that may be necessary for the due and proper conduct of the chit.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any dispute arises with regard to the value of the property offered as security under`
  line `clause (e) of sub-section (1), it shall be referred to the Registrar for arbitration under section 64.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 3, for "chit amount" (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 8, for "five per cent." (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `3. The word "and" omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (32098)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Duties of foreman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32098&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The foreman shall, on the prized subscriber furnishing sufficient`
  line `security for the due payment of future subscriptions, be bound to pay him the ^1[net chit amount]::`
  line
  line `Provided that the prized subscriber shall be entitled to the payment of the ^1[net chit amount] without any`
  line `security whatsoever if he agrees to the deduction therefrom of the amount of all future subscriptions and`
  line `in such a case, the foreman shall pay the ^1[net chit amount] to the prized subscriber within seven days after the`
  line `date of the draw or before the date of the next succeeding instalment, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the ^1[net chit amount] has been paid to the prized subscriber under the first`
  line `proviso, the amount deducted shall be deposited by the foreman in an approved bank mentioned in the`
  line `chit agreement and he shall not withdraw the amount so deposited except for the payment of future`
  line subscriptions.
  line
  line `(2) If, owing to the default of the prized subscriber, the ^1[net chit amount] due in respect of any draw`
  line `remains unpaid until the date of the next succeeding instalment, the foreman shall deposit the prize`
  line `amount forthwith in a separate account in an approved bank mentioned in the chit agreement and intimate`
  line `in writing the fact of such deposit and the reasons therefor to the prized subscriber and the Registrar:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any prized subscriber does not collect the ^1[net chit amount] in respect of any`
  line `instalment of a chit within a period of two months from the date of the draw, it shall be open to the`
  line `foreman to hold another draw in respect of such instalment.`
  line
  line `(3) Every payment of the ^1[net chit amount] or the amount of future subscriptions under sub-section (1),`
  line `and the deposit of the ^1[net chit amount] under sub-section (2), shall be intimated to the subscribers at the next`
  line `succeeding draw and the particulars of such payment or deposit shall be entered in the minutes of the`
  line `proceedings of that draw.`
  line
  line `(4) The foreman shall not appropriate to himself any amount in excess of what he is entitled to under`
  line `clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 21:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the foreman is himself a prized subscriber, he shall be entitled to appropriate to`
  line `himself the ^1[net chit amount] subject to his complying with the provisions of section 31:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the foreman may appropriate to himself the interest accruing on the amount`
  line `deposited under the second proviso to sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) The foreman shall not admit any person as a subscriber to a chit, if, by such admission, the total`
  line `number of tickets mentioned in the chit agreement is increased.`
  line
  line `(6) The foreman shall distribute among the subscribers, in accordance with the chit agreement, the`
  line `^2[share of discount] either in cash, grain or by way of adjustment towards the subscriptions payable for the next`
  line `instalment, if any.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “prize amount” (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “dividend” (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (32099)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Books, records, etc., to be kept by foreman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32099&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The foreman shall maintain in his registered`
  line `office, or, as the case may be, in the place or the principal place of his business, or, where the foreman has`
  line `any branch office, sub-office or any place of business for the conduct of chit business in a State other than`
  line `the State in which his registered office or the principal place of his business is situated, in such branch`
  line `office, sub-office or place of business in respect of the business conducted in that State--`
  line
  line `(a) a register containing--`
  line
  line `(i) the names and full particulars of the subscribers in each chit together with the number of`
  line `tickets held by each subscriber;`
  line
  line `(ii) the dates on which the subscribers signed the chit agreement; and`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of an assignment of a ticket by a subscriber, the name and full address of the`
  line `assignee with the date of assignment and the date on which the assignment had been recognised`
  line `by the foreman;`
  line
  line `(b) a book containing the minutes of the proceedings of each draw;`
  line
  line `(c) a ledger containing--`
  line
  line `(i) the amounts paid by the subscribers in each chit and the dates of such payments;`
  line
  line `(ii) the amounts paid to the prized subscribers and the dates of such payments; and`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of any deposit in an approved bank mentioned in the chit agreement, the date`
  line `and the amount of such deposit;`
  line
  line `(d) a register in the prescribed form showing the amounts deposited in approved banks as`
  line `required under the provisions of this Act in respect of all chits conducted by the foreman at his office;`
  line and
  line
  line `(e) such other registers and books in such form as may be prescribed by the State Government`
  line `within whose jurisdiction the chit is conducted.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (32100)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Balance sheet.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32100&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956),`
  line `every foreman shall prepare and file with the Registrar within such time as may be prescribed, a`
  line `balance sheet as on the last date of each calendar year, or, as the case may be, the financial year of the`
  line `foreman, and a profit and loss account relating to the year of account, in the forms set out in Parts I and II`
  line `of the Schedule, or as near thereto as circumstances admit, in respect of the chit business and audited by`
  line `auditors qualified to act as auditors under the Companies Act, 1956, or by a chit auditor appointed under`
  line `section 61:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a balance sheet is audited by an auditor qualified to act as auditor under the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), a chit auditor appointed under section 61 shall have the right to audit`
  line `the balance sheet at any time if so authorised by the Registrar in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (32101)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Liability of foreman to subscribers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32101&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every foreman shall be liable to account to the`
  line `subscribers for the amounts due to them.`
  line
  line `(2) Where there are more than one foreman in a chit, each one of them jointly and severally and, if the`
  line `foreman is a firm or other association of individuals, each one of the partners or individuals thereof jointly`
  line `and severally and, if the foreman is a company, the company as such, shall be liable to the subscribers in`
  line `respect of the obligations arising out of the chit.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (32102)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Withdrawal of foreman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32102&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No foreman, or where there are more than one foreman in a chit,`
  line `none of them shall withdraw from the chit until its termination unless such withdrawal is assented to in`
  line `writing by all the non-prized and unpaid prized subscribers and a copy of such assent has been filed with`
  line `the Registrar under section 41.`
  line
  line `(2) The withdrawal from a chit of any one of the foreman shall not affect the security given by him`
  line `under section 20 or section 31.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (32103)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Non-prized subscribers to pay subscriptions and obtain receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32103&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Every non-prized`
  line `subscriber shall pay his subscription due in respect of every instalment on the dates and times and at the`
  line `places mentioned in the chit agreement and shall, on such payment, be entitled to obtain a receipt from the`
  line foreman.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (32104)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Removal of defaulting subscribers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32104&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) A non-prized subscriber who defaults in paying his`
  line `subscription in accordance with the terms of the chit agreement shall be liable to have his name removed`
  line `from the list of subscribers and a written notice of such removal shall be given by the foreman to the`
  line `defaulting subscriber within fourteen days of the date of such removal:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the defaulter pays the defaulted instalment with interest at such rate as may be`
  line `prescribed within seven days of the date of receipt of such notice, his name shall be re-entered in the list`
  line `of such subscribers.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such removal under sub-section (1) shall with the date thereof be entered in the relevant`
  line `book maintained by the foreman.`
  line
  line `(3) A true copy of the entry referred to in sub-section (2) shall be filed by the foreman with the`
  line `Registrar within fourteen days from the date of removal.`
  line
  line `(4) Any defaulting subscriber aggrieved by the removal of his name from the list of subscribers may,`
  line `within seven days of the date of receipt of the notice of removal refer the matter to the Registrar for`
  line `arbitration under section 64.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (32105)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Substitution of subscribers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32105&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) A foreman may substitute in the list of subscribers any person`
  line `(thereafter in this Chapter referred to as the substituted subscriber) in place of the defaulting subscriber`
  line `whose name has been removed under sub-section (1) of section 28.`
  line
  line `(2) Every substitution referred to in sub-section (1) shall, with the date thereof, be entered in the`
  line `relevant book maintained by the foreman and a true copy of every such entry shall be filed by the foreman`
  line `with the Registrar within fourteen days from the date of substitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (32106)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Amounts due to defaulting subscribers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32106&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) A foreman shall, out of the amounts payable by`
  line `and realized from the substituted subscriber towards the instalments relatable to the period before the date`
  line `of the substitution (including the arrears due from the defaulting subscriber), deposit, before the date of`
  line `the next succeeding instalment, in a separate identifiable account in an approved bank mentioned in the`
  line `chit agreement, an amount equal to the contributions made by the defaulting subscriber less such`
  line `deductions as may be provided for in the chit agreement, and shall inform the defaulting subscriber as`
  line `well as the Registrar of the fact of such deposit and shall not withdraw the amount so deposited except for`
  line `payment to the defaulting subscriber.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount so deposited under sub-section (1) shall be paid to the defaulting subscriber as and`
  line `when he claims the amount and the amount so deposited shall not be withdrawn by the foreman for any`
  line `purpose other than for such payment.`
  line
  line `(3) The contributions of any defaulting subscriber who has not been substituted till the termination of`
  line `the chit shall be paid to him within fifteen days from the date of termination of the chit subject to such`
  line `deductions as may be provided for in the chit agreement.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (32107)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Prized subscriber to furnish security.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 3, for “prize amount” (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32107&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Every prized subscriber shall, if he has not offered to`
  line `deduct the amount of all future subscriptions from the ^1[net chit amount] due to him, furnish, and a foreman`
  line `shall take, sufficient security for the due payment of all future subscriptions and, if the foreman is a prized`
  line `subscriber, he shall give security for the due payment of all the future subscriptions to the satisfaction of`
  line `the Registrar.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (32108)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Prized subscriber to pay subscriptions regularly.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32108&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Every prized subscriber shall pay his`
  line `subscriptions regularly on the dates and times and at the place mentioned in the chit agreement and, on his`
  line `failure to do so, he shall be liable to make a consolidated payment of all the future subscriptions`
  line forthwith.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (32109)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Foreman to demand future subscriptions by written notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32109&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `A foreman shall not be entitled`
  line `to claim a consolidated payment from a defaulting prized subscriber under section 32 unless he makes a`
  line `demand to that effect in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a dispute is raised under this Act by a foreman for a consolidated payment of future`
  line `subscriptions from a defaulting prized subscriber and if the subscriber pays to the foreman on or before`
  line `the date to which the dispute is posted for hearing the arrears of subscriptions till that date together with`
  line `the interest thereon at the rate provided for in the chit agreement and the cost of adjudication of the`
  line `dispute, the Registrar or his nominee hearing the dispute shall, notwithstanding any contract to the`
  line `contrary, make an order directing the subscriber to pay to the foreman the future subscriptions on or`
  line `before the dates on which they fall due, and that, in case of any default of such payments by the`
  line `subscriber, the foreman shall be at liberty to realise, in execution of that order, all future subscriptions and`
  line `interest together with the costs, if any, less the amount, if any, already paid by the subscriber in respect`
  line `thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any such dispute is on a promissory note, no order shall be passed under this`
  line `sub-section unless such promissory note expressly states that the amount due under the promissory note is`
  line `towards the payment of subscriptions to the chit.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who holds any interest in the property furnished as security or part thereof, shall be`
  line `entitled to make the payment under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) All consolidated payments of future subscriptions realised by a foreman shall be deposited by him`
  line `in an approved bank mentioned in the chit agreement before the date of the succeeding instalment and the`
  line `amount so deposited shall not be withdrawn except for payment of future subscriptions.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any property is obtained as security in lieu of the consolidated payment of future`
  line `subscriptions, it shall remain as security for the due payment of future subscriptions.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (32110)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Restrictions on transfer of rights of foreman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32110&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) No transfer of the rights of a foreman to`
  line `receive subscriptions from the prized subscribers shall be made without the previous sanction in writing`
  line `of the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(2) Any transfer of the rights of a foreman to receive subscriptions from the prized subscribers shall,`
  line `if it is likely to defeat or delay the interests of a non-prized or unpaid prized subscriber, be voidable at the`
  line `instance of such subscriber.`
  line
  line `(3) When under sub-section (2), a transfer is disputed by a subscriber, the burden of proving that the`
  line `foreman was in solvent in circumstances at the time of the transfer and that the transfer does not defeat or`
  line `delay the interests of such subscriber is on the transferee.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (32111)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Transfer of non-prized subscriber's rights to be in writing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32111&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Every transfer by a non-prized`
  line `subscriber of his rights in the chit shall be in writing duly attested by at least two witnesses and shall be`
  line `filed with the foreman.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (32112)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Recognition of transfer by foreman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32112&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Every transfer under section 35 shall, within a period of`
  line `fourteen days from the date of receipt of the proposal for transfer by the foreman, be recognised by him`
  line `unless the transferee is not solvent or the transfer was effected with a view to defeating the provisions of`
  line `any law including this Act and the decision of the foreman to recognise the transfer or not shall forthwith`
  line `be communicated to the parties concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (32113)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Entry of transferee's name in the books.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32113&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Every transfer under section 34 or section 35 shall`
  line `be entered by the foreman in the books of the chit forthwith and a true copy of such entry shall be filed by`
  line `the foreman with the Registrar within fourteen days from the date of making such entry.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (32114)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Meetings of general body of subscribers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32114&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The foreman may, on his own motion, convene a`
  line `special meeting of the general body of subscribers for considering any proposal to pass a special`
  line resolution.
  line
  line `(2) The foreman shall convene such a meeting on the requisition in writing of not less than`
  line `twenty-five per cent. of the number of non-prized and unpaid prized subscribers, and the meeting so`
  line `convened shall be held within thirty days of the date of receipt of the requisition and if the foreman`
  line `refused or fails to call such a meeting within fourteen days of the date of receipt of such requisition, not`
  line `less than twenty-five per cent. of the number of non-prized and unpaid prized subscribers may give notice`
  line `of the fact to the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall, within twenty-one days of the receipt of the notice under sub-section (2),`
  line `convene or direct the convening of a special meeting of the general body of the subscribers and on receipt`
  line `of such a direction, it shall be the duty of the foreman to comply with such direction.`
  line
  line `(4) Notice of not less than fourteen days shall be given to all the subscribers of a meeting under this`
  line `section specifying the object, date, hour and place of meeting and a copy of the special resolution shall`
  line `also be sent along with the notice of the meeting.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section and section 39, "special resolution" means a resolution`
  line `which is passed at a meeting of the general body of the subscribers specially convened for the purpose, by`
  line `a majority of not less than two-thirds of the subscribers to the chit present at the meeting in person or by`
  line `proxy and representing not less than three-fourths of the amount or, as the case may be, the value of the`
  line `grain, subscribed by all the non-prized and unpaid prized subscribers, if any.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (32115)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Provision for continuation of chits in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32115&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a foreman dies or becomes of`
  line `unsound mind or is otherwise incapacitated, the chit may continue in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `the chit agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a foreman is adjudicated an insolvent, or withdraws from the chit under section 26, or fails`
  line `to conduct the chit at any instalment or on any other date before the next succeeding instalment as may`
  line `have been agreed upon by a special resolution, any one or more of such subscribers authorised by such`
  line `resolution may, in the absence of any provision in the chit agreement for the future conduct of the chit,`
  line `take the place of the foreman and continue the chit or make other arrangements for the further conduct of`
  line `the chit.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (32116)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Termination of chits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32116&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `A chit shall be deemed to have terminated,`
  line
  line `(a) when the period specified therefor in the chit agreement has expired provided the payment of`
  line `dues to all the subscribers has been completed; or`
  line
  line `(b) when all the non-prized and unpaid prized subscribers and the foreman consent in writing to`
  line `the termination of the chit and a copy of such consent is filed with the Registrar as required under`
  line `section 41; or`
  line
  line `(c) where a foreman dies or becomes of unsound mind or is otherwise incapacitated and the chit`
  line `is not continued in accordance with the provisions of the chit agreement:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in a case where the foreman is a firm, if a partner thereof dies or becomes of unsound`
  line `mind or is otherwise incapacitated, the chit shall not be deemed to have terminated and the surviving`
  line `partner or partners shall conduct the chit in the absence of any provision to the contrary in the chit`
  line agreement.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (32117)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Copy of assent or consent to be filed with Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32117&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `A true copy of every assent referred to`
  line `in section 26 and of every consent referred to in clause (b) of section 40 with their dates shall be filed by`
  line `the foreman or by the surviving partner or partners, as the case may be, with the Registrar within fourteen`
  line `days from the date of such assent or consent.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (32118)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Refund of non-prized subscribers' subscriptions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 3, for “dividend” (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32118&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Except in the cases referred to in`
  line `clauses (a) and (b) of section 40,--`
  line
  line `(a) every non-prized subscriber shall, unless otherwise provided for in this Act or in the chit`
  line `agreement, be entitled to get back his subscriptions at the termination of the chit without any`
  line `deduction for ^1[share of discount], if any, earned by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that, any person to whom the rights of a non-prized subscriber are transferred in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 35, shall, in addition to his own subscriptions, be entitled to`
  line `get back the subscriptions paid by such non-prized subscriber, subject to the conditions specified in`
  line `this section;`
  line
  line `(b) if a chit terminates on a date earlier than the date originally fixed in the chit agreement, the`
  line `non-prized subscribers claim shall be deemed to have arisen on the date on which he has notice`
  line thereof.
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (32119)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Subscribers' dues to be first charge on chit assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32119&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Any amount due to the subscriber from a`
  line `foreman in relation to the chit business shall be a first charge on the chit assets.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (32120)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Foreman to allow certain subscribers to inspect chit records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32120&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Every foreman shall, on`
  line `payment of such fee not exceeding five rupees as may be specified in the chit agreement, allow the`
  line `non-prized subscribers and unpaid prized subscribers reasonable facilities on all the dates of draw or on`
  line `such other dates and within such hours as may be provided for in the chit agreement, for the inspection of`
  line `security bonds and documents, receipts and other records taken from the prized subscribers or furnished`
  line `by the foreman as a subscriber and all chit records, including books of account, pass books, balance sheet`
  line `and profit and loss accounts and such other records as may show the actual financial position of the chit.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (32121)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Preservation of chit records by foreman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32121&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `All the records pertaining to a chit shall be kept by`
  line `the foreman for a period of eight years from the date of termination of the chit.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (32122)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Inspection of chit books and records by Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32122&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `sections 209 and 209A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), the Registrar or an officer authorised by`
  line `the State Government in this behalf may inspect chit books and all the records of a chit during working`
  line `hours on any working day at the premises of the foreman with or without giving notice and it shall be the`
  line `duty of every foreman to produce to the Registrar or the officer so authorised, all such books and records`
  line `as are in his custody or power and to furnish him with any statement or information relating to the chits as`
  line `he may require from the foreman within such time as he may specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar or an officer authorised by the State Government in this behalf may, after giving`
  line `seven days' notice in writing to the foreman, direct him to produce before him for inspection such chit`
  line `books and records as he may require at the time and place mentioned in the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) If on an inspection made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), any defects are found, the`
  line `Registrar may bring such defects to the notice of the foreman and may also make an order directing the`
  line `foreman to take such action as may be specified in the order to remedy the defects within the time`
  line `specified therein.`
  line
  line `(4) Every foreman shall be bound to comply with the directions contained in an order made under`
  line `sub-section (3).`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (32123)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power of Reserve Bank to inspect chit books and records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32123&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in section 46 shall be`
  line `deemed to affect the power of the Reserve Bank to inspect the books and records of any foreman under`
  line `the provisions of section 45N of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934).`
  line
  line `(2) The Reserve Bank may, if it considers necessary, forward a copy of its report or of any part of its`
  line `report on the inspection of the books and records of a foreman to the foreman for taking necessary action.`
  line
  line `(3) Every foreman shall, on receipt of the report or part thereof under sub-section (2), be bound to`
  line `comply with the directions, if any, given by the Reserve Bank in this behalf and shall, if so required,`
  line `submit periodical reports in regard to the action taken by him.`
  line
  line `(4) The Reserve Bank may also forward a copy of the report on the inspection of the books and`
  line `records of a foreman to the State Government within whose jurisdiction the registered office of the`
  line `company, if the foreman is a company, or the place or the principal place of business of the foreman in`
  line `any other case, is situated for such action as may be considered necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (32124)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Circumstances under which chits may be wound up.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 3, for “prize amount” (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32124&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `A chit may be wound up by the`
  line `Registrar within whose territorial jurisdiction the chit has been registered, either on his own motion or on`
  line `an application made by any non-prized or unpaid prized subscriber,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the chit has terminated under clause (c) of section 40; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the foreman commits any such act in respect of the security specified in section 20 as is`
  line `calculated to impair materially the nature of the security or the value thereof; or`
  line
  line `(c) if he fails to deposit any amount required to be deposited under any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it is proved to the satisfaction of the Registrar that the foreman is unable to pay the amounts`
  line `due to the subscribers; or`
  line
  line `(e) if the execution or other process issued on an order passed by the Registrar in favour of any`
  line `subscriber in respect of amounts due to him from the foreman in relation to the chit business is`
  line `returned unsatisfied in whole or in part; or`
  line
  line `(f) if it is proved that there has been a fraud or collusion on the part of the foreman in the matter`
  line `of taking securities from any prized subscriber; or`
  line
  line `(g) if the foreman has appropriated the ^1[net chit amount] in his capacity as a subscriber without`
  line `furnishing sufficient security for future subscriptions; or`
  line
  line `(h) if the Registrar is satisfied that the affairs of the chit are being conducted in a manner`
  line `prejudicial to the interests of the subscribers; or`
  line
  line `(i) if it is just and equitable that the chit should be wound up.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of clause (d), in determining whether the foreman is unable to pay the`
  line `amounts due to the subscribers, the Registrar shall take into account his contingent and future liabilities in`
  line `respect of the chit.`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (32125)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Application for winding up.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32125&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `An application for the winding up of a chit shall be made by a`
  line `petition presented by any non-prized or unpaid prized subscriber to the Registrar signed and verified in`
  line `the manner laid down by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), and shall contain such particulars`
  line `as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application for the winding up of a chit under clause (d) or clause (i) of section 48`
  line `shall lie unless such application is presented,--`
  line
  line `(a) by non-prized and unpaid prized subscribers representing not less than twenty-five per cent. of`
  line `the amount or, as the case may be, the value of the grain subscribed by all the non-prized and unpaid`
  line `prized subscribers, if any; or`
  line
  line `(b) with the previous sanction of the State Government within whose jurisdiction the chit is`
  line `commenced or conducted.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of clause (a), of the proviso, a subscriber of a fraction of a ticket`
  line `shall be deemed to be a subscriber only to the extent of such fraction.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (32126)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Bar to winding up proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32126&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 48 and 49, no`
  line `petition for the winding up of a chit shall be entertained by the Registrar,--`
  line
  line `(a) if proceedings relating to insolvency are pending against the foreman; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the foreman is a firm, if proceedings relating to insolvency are pending against all the`
  line `partners or all the partners except one thereof, or proceedings for the dissolution of the firm are`
  line `pending; or`
  line
  line `(c) where the foreman is a company or co-operative society, if proceedings for the winding up of`
  line `such company or co-operative society are pending.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (32127)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Commencement and effect of winding up order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32127&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `An order for the winding up of a chit shall`
  line `operate in favour of all the subscribers to whom amounts are due from the foreman and it shall be deemed`
  line `to have commenced from the date of the presentation of the application for the winding up.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (32128)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Injunction order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32128&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar may, on the application of the foreman or of any subscriber to`
  line `whom amounts are due in respect of a chit, at any time after the presentation of the application for the`
  line `winding up of the chit under this Act and before the making of an order for the appointment of an interim`
  line `receiver or for the winding up of the chit, restrain any other proceedings instituted against the foreman for`
  line `the realisation of amounts due from him on such terms as the Registrar thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (32129)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Powers of Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32129&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar may, after hearing an application under this Chapter,`
  line `dismiss it with or without costs, or adjourn the hearing conditionally or unconditionally or make an`
  line `interim or any other order that he deems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (32130)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Vesting of chit assets in Registrar or other persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32130&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `On the making of an order for the`
  line `winding up of a chit, all the chit assets pertaining to such chit shall vest in the Registrar or in any person`
  line `appointed by him for distribution amongst the subscribers to whom amounts are due in respect of the chit.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (32131)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Suits, etc., to be stayed on winding up order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32131&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `When a winding up order has been made or a`
  line `receiver has been appointed, no suit or other legal proceedings shall be continued or commenced against`
  line `the foreman by a subscriber for the realisation of amounts due to him in respect of the chit except with the`
  line `leave of the Registrar winding up the chit and on such terms as he may impose.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (32132)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Notification of winding up order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32132&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `On the making of a winding up order, the Registrar shall`
  line `make an entry in his book relating to the chit and shall notify in the Official Gazette that the order has`
  line `been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (32133)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Cessation of winding up proceedings on insolvency of foreman, etc., or the winding up of the company and transfer of such proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32133&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `Where during the pendency of the proceedings for the`
  line `winding up of a chit, the foreman is adjudicated an insolvent, or where the foreman is a firm, all the`
  line `partners or all the partners except one thereof are adjudicated insolvents, or where the foreman is a`
  line `company, the company has been ordered to be wound up by the Court, the winding up proceedings under`
  line `this Chapter shall cease and the distribution of the chit assets shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `sections 43 and 52, be made by the insolvency court or the court winding up the company, as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (32134)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Award of compensation to foreman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32134&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an application for the winding up of a chit is`
  line `dismissed and the Registrar is satisfied that the petition is frivolous or vexatious, he may, on the`
  line `application of the foreman, award against the petitioner such amount, not exceeding one thousand rupees,`
  line `as he deems reasonable as compensation to the foreman for the expenses or injury caused to him by the`
  line `presentation of the application and the proceedings thereon, and such amount may be realised as if the`
  line `award were a decree of a Civil Court.`
  line
  line `(2) On the making of an award under sub-section (1), no suit for compensation in respect of an`
  line `application for any winding up of the chit shall be entertained.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (32135)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Right to appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32135&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `The foreman or any subscriber or any other person aggrieved by a decision or`
  line `order of the Registrar in any proceedings for the winding up of a chit may, within sixty days from the date`
  line `of such decision or order, appeal to the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (32136)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 3, for "dividend" (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32136&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an order refusing to wind up a chit has been made under this Act, the`
  line `chit shall be deemed to have been under suspension from the date of presentation of the application to the`
  line `date of such order in respect of non-prized subscribers; and, notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `chit agreement, no non-prized subscriber who was not a defaulter on the date of the presentation of the`
  line `petition for winding up, shall be deemed to be a defaulter on the date of such order.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order refusing to wind up a chit has been made under this Act, in computing the period`
  line `of limitation prescribed for any suit or other legal proceedings (other than a suit or application in respect`
  line `of which the leave of the court has been obtained) which might have been brought or instituted, but for`
  line `the presentation of the application for the winding up of the chit, the period from the date of the`
  line `presentation of the application to the date of the order refusing to wind up a chit shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this Chapter shall affect the rights of a subscriber to proceed against the`
  line `foreman personally for the balance, if any, of the amount due to him after the declaration of the final`
  line `^1[share of discount] in the proceedings for the winding up of the chit and in computing the period of limitation`
  line `prescribed for any such proceedings, the period from the date of the presentation of the application for the`
  line `winding up of the chit to the date of the declaration of the final ^1[share of discount] shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (32137)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Appointment of Registrar and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 3, for “chit amount” (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32137&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, appoint a Registrar of Chits and as many Additional, Joint, Deputy and Assistant`
  line `Registrars as may be necessary for the purpose of discharging the duties imposed upon the Registrar by or`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar may appoint as many inspectors of chits and chit auditors as may be necessary for`
  line `the purpose of discharging the duties imposed on the inspectors of chits or chit auditors by or under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(3) All inspectors of chits and chit auditors shall discharge the duties imposed upon them by or under`
  line `this Act under the general superintendence and control of the Registrar.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Registrar is of the opinion that the accounts of any chit are not properly maintained and that`
  line `such accounts should be audited, it shall be lawful for him to have such accounts audited by a chit auditor.`
  line
  line `(5) It shall be the duty of the foreman of the chit whose accounts are to be audited by a chit auditor`
  line `under sub-section (4) to produce before the chit auditor, all accounts, books and other records relating to`
  line `the chit, to furnish him with such information as may be required and afford him all such assistance and`
  line `facilities as may be necessary and reasonable in regard to the audit of the accounts of the chit.`
  line
  line `(6) The foreman shall pay to the chit auditor such fees as may be prescribed for the audit of the`
  line `accounts of the chit under sub-section (4):`
  line
  line `Provided that different scales of fees may be prescribed for different chits depending on the quantum`
  line `of the ^1[gross chit amount].`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (32138)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Inspection of documents in Registrar's office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32138&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `The foreman of a chit or any subscriber in a`
  line `chit or the heirs or legal representatives of any foreman or subscriber may, on payment of such fees as`
  line `may be prescribed,--`
  line
  line `(a) inspect the documents of the concerned chit kept by the Registrar; or`
  line
  line `(b) obtain a certified copy or on extract of any such document or record.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (32139)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Levy of fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32139&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be paid to the Registrar such fees as the State Government may,`
  line `from time to time, prescribe for,--`
  line
  line `(a) the issue of previous sanction under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the filing of the chit agreement with the Registrar and the registration of the chit under`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the filing of a declaration with the Registrar and the grant of a certificate of commencement`
  line `under section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) the filing of copies of documents under any of the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) the audit of the accounts of the foreman under section 61;`
  line
  line `(f) the inspection of documents under section 62;`
  line
  line `(g) the obtaining of certified copies or extracts of documents and records under section 62; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other matters as may appear necessary to the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A table of fees prescribed under sub-section (1) shall be exhibited on a notice board in the office`
  line `of the Registrar.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (32140)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Disputes relating to chit business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32140&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for`
  line `the time being in force, any dispute touching the management of a chit business shall be referred by any`
  line `of the parties to the dispute, to the Registrar for arbitration if each party thereto is one or the other of the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a foreman, a prized subscriber or a non-prized subscriber, including a defaulting subscriber,`
  line `past subscriber or a person claiming through a subscriber, or a deceased subscriber to a chit;`
  line
  line `(b) a surety of a subscriber, past subscriber, or a deceased subscriber.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this sub-section, a dispute touching the management of a chit`
  line `business shall include`
  line
  line `(i) a claim by or against a foreman for any debt or demand due to him from a subscriber, or due`
  line `from him to a subscriber, past subscriber or the nominee, heir or legal representative of a deceased`
  line `subscriber whether such debt or demand is admitted or not;`
  line
  line `(ii) a claim by a surety for any sum or demand due to him from the principal borrower in respect`
  line `of a loan by a foreman and recovered from the surety owing to the default of the principal borrower,`
  line `whether such sum or demand is admitted or not; and`
  line
  line `(iii) a refusal or failure by a subscriber, past subscriber or the nominee, heir or legal`
  line `representative of a deceased subscriber to deliver possession to a foreman of land or any other asset`
  line `resumed by him for breach of conditions of the assignment.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any question arises as to whether any matter referred to for the award of the Registrar is a`
  line `dispute or not for the purposes of sub-section (1), the same shall be decided by the Registrar whose`
  line `decision thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) No Civil Court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or other proceedings in respect of any`
  line `dispute referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (32141)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Period of limitation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32141&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Limitation`
  line `Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), but subject to the specific provisions contained in this Act, the period of`
  line `limitation in the case of a dispute referred to the Registrar under section 64, shall`
  line
  line `(a) if the dispute relates to the recovery of any sum, including interest thereon, due to a foreman`
  line `from a deceased subscriber, be three years, computed from the date on which such subscriber dies or`
  line `ceases to be a subscriber; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the dispute is between a foreman and a subscriber or a past subscriber, or the nominee, heir`
  line `or legal representative of a deceased subscriber, and the dispute relates to any act or omission on the`
  line `part of either party to the dispute, be three years from the date on which the act or omission with`
  line `reference to which the dispute arose, took place.`
  line
  line `(2) The period of limitation in the case of any dispute other than those referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `which are required to be referred to the Registrar under section 64 shall be regulated by the provisions of`
  line `the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), as if the dispute were a suit, and the Registrar, a Civil Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), the Registrar may admit a dispute`
  line `after the expiry of the period of limitation specified therein, if the applicant satisfies the Registrar that he`
  line `had sufficient cause for not referring the dispute within such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (32142)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Settlement of disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32142&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Registrar is satisfied that any matter referred to him or`
  line `brought to his notice is a dispute within the meaning of section 64, he shall, subject to such rules as may`
  line `be prescribed, settle the dispute himself, or refer it for disposal to a person appointed by him (hereafter in`
  line `this Chapter referred to as the nominee).`
  line
  line `(2) Where any dispute is referred under sub-section (1) for settlement to the nominee, the Registrar`
  line `may, at any time for reasons to be recorded in writing, withdraw such dispute from the nominee and may`
  line `settle the dispute himself, or refer it again for settlement to any other nominee appointed by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (32143)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Procedure for settlement of disputes and powers of Registrar or nominee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32143&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar`
  line `or the nominee hearing a dispute under section 66, shall, in addition to the powers conferred on him under`
  line `that section, have the same powers as are vested in a Civil Court while trying a suit under the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of persons and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and inspection of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copies thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Except with the permission of the Registrar or the nominee, no party shall be represented at the`
  line `hearing of a dispute by a legal practitioner.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) If the Registrar or the nominee is satisfied that any person, whether he is a subscriber or not,`
  line `has acquired any interest in the property of a person who is a party to a dispute, he may order that the`
  line `person who has acquired the interest in the property may be joined as a party to the dispute, and any`
  line `decision that may be given by the Registrar or the nominee on the dispute shall be binding on the party so`
  line `joined, in the same manner as if he were an original party to the dispute.`
  line
  line `(b) Where a dispute has been referred in the name of a wrong person, or where all the necessary`
  line `parties have not been included, the Registrar or the nominee may, if he is satisfied that it was due to a`
  line `genuine mistake, order any other person to be substituted or added as parties to the dispute at any stage of`
  line `hearing of the dispute on such terms as he thinks just.`
  line
  line `(c) The Registrar or the nominee may, at any stage of the proceedings, either upon or without the`
  line `application of either party and on such terms as may appear to the Registrar or the nominee to be just,`
  line `order that the name of any party improperly joined be struck off.`
  line
  line `(d) Any person who is a party to the dispute and entitled to more than one relief in respect of the same`
  line `cause of action may claim all or any such reliefs, but if he omits to claim any such relief, he shall not be`
  line `entitled to claim that relief, except with the leave of the Registrar or the nominee.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (32144)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Attachment before judgment and other interlocutory orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32144&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a dispute has been`
  line `referred under section 64 and the Registrar or the nominee hearing the dispute is satisfied on enquiry or`
  line `otherwise that a party to such dispute, with intent to defeat or obstruct the execution of any award or the`
  line `carrying out of any order that may be made,--`
  line
  line `(a) is about to dispose of the whole or any part of his property; or`
  line
  line `(b) is about to remove the whole or any part of the property from the jurisdiction of the Registrar,`
  line
  line `he may, unless adequate security is furnished, direct conditional attachment of the said property, and such`
  line `attachment shall have the same effect as if it is made by a competent Civil Court.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Registrar or the nominee directs the attachment of any property under sub-section (1),`
  line `he shall issue a notice calling upon the person whose property is so attached to furnish such security as he`
  line `thinks adequate within a specified period, and if the person fails to provide such security, the Registrar or`
  line `the nominee may confirm the order, and may, after the decision in the dispute, direct the disposal of the`
  line `property so attached towards the claim, if awarded.`
  line
  line `(3) Any attachment made under this section shall not affect the rights, subsisting prior to the`
  line `attachment of the property, of persons who are not parties to the dispute, or bar any person holding a`
  line `decree against the person whose property is so attached from applying for the sale of the property under`
  line `the attachment of such decree.`
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar or the nominee may, in order to prevent the ends of justice being defeated, make`
  line `such interlocutory orders pending the award in a dispute referred to in sub-section (1) as may appear to be`
  line `just and convenient.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (32145)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Decision of Registrar or nominee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32145&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `When a dispute is referred to arbitration under this Chapter,`
  line `the Registrar or the nominee, may, after giving a reasonable opportunity to the parties to the dispute to be`
  line `heard, make an award on the dispute, on the expenses incurred by the parties to the dispute in connection`
  line `with the proceedings and the fees and expenses payable to the Registrar or the nominee, and such an`
  line `award shall not be invalid merely on the ground that it was made after the expiry of the period, if any,`
  line `fixed for deciding the dispute by the Registrar, and shall, subject to appeal under section 70, be final and`
  line `binding on the parties to the dispute.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (32146)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Appeal against decision of Registrar or nominee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32146&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Any party aggrieved by any order passed`
  line `by the Registrar or the nominee or the award of the Registrar or the nominee under section 69, may,`
  line `within two months from the date of the order or award, appeal to the State Government.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line [Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 70.--In the Chit Funds Act, 1982 (Central Act 40 of 1982) (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the principal Act),--`
  line
  line `(i) section 70 shall be renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof and in sub-section (1) as so renumbered,`
  line `after the words "State Government", the words "or to such officer or authority, as may be empowered by`
  line `notification by the State Government, in that behalf" shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(ii) after sub-section (1) as so renumbered, the following shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) The State Government or such officer or authority aforesaid may, after giving the appellant`
  line `an opportunity of making his representation, pass such orders on the appeals as it or he thinks fit and`
  line `such order shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) All appeals pending before the State Government, on such date of notification empowering`
  line `such officer or authority, shall be transferred to such officer or authority and shall be disposed off as`
  line `if it has been filed before such authority."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 2 of 2008, s. 2.]`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (32147)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Money how recovered.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32147&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Every order passed by the Registrar or the nominee under section 68 or`
  line `section 69 and every order passed by the State Government in appeal under section 70 for payment of any`
  line `money shall, if not carried out,--`
  line
  line `(a) on a certificate issued by the Registrar, be deemed to be a decree of a Civil Court, and shall be`
  line `executed in the same manner as a decree of such Court, or`
  line
  line `(b) be executed in accordance with the provisions of any law for the time being in force for the`
  line `recovery of amounts as arrears of land revenue:`
  line
  line `Provided that no application for execution under clause (b) shall be made after the expiry of three`
  line `years from the date fixed in the order, and if no such date is fixed, from the date of the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (32148)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Private transfer of property made after issue of certificate void against foreman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32148&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `private transfer of delivery of, or encumbrance or charge on, property made or created after the issue of`
  line `the certificate by the Registrar under section 71 shall be null and void against the foreman on whose`
  line `application the said certificate was issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (32149)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Advisory role of Reserve Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32149&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `The Reserve Bank may tender to any State Government such`
  line `advice on questions of policy with respect to this Act as it thinks fit either on its own motion or on a`
  line `request made by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (32150)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32150&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any foreman aggrieved by the decision of the Registrar,--`
  line
  line `(a) refusing to register the chit agreement under section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) refusing to grant a certificate of commencement under sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) refusing to accept any security under sub-section (1) of section 20 or under section 31; or`
  line
  line `(d) refusing to release the security charged under section 20 or section 31,`
  line
  line `may, within thirty days of the communication to him of such decision, appeal to the State Government or`
  line `to such officer or authority as may be empowered by notification in the Official Gazette by the State`
  line `Government in that behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Any foreman or other person aggrieved by the order of the Registrar under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 34 may, within thirty days of the communication to him of such decision, appeal to the State`
  line `Government or to such officer or authority as may be empowered by notification in the Official Gazette`
  line `by the State Government in that behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government or such officer or authority aforesaid may, after giving the appellant an`
  line `opportunity of making his representation, pass such order on the appeal as it or he thinks fit and such`
  line `order shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (32151)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Powers of Registrar to give extension of time for filing documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32151&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar may, in his`
  line `discretion and upon an application in writing by a foreman made within the period specified for the filing`
  line `of documents, under sub-section (3) of section 28, sub-section (2) of section 29, section 37 or section 41,`
  line `allow the foreman further time not exceeding fifteen days to file copies of such documents.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (32152)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32152&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever contravenes or abets the contravention of any of the provisions of`
  line `sections 4, 5, 8, 9, 11, 12, 13, 14, 19, 20, 22, 24, 30, 31, sub-section (4) of section 33, sections 46, 47 or`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 61 shall, on conviction, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Any foreman,--`
  line
  line `(a) who fails to file any document required to be fied under this Act within the period specified`
  line `therefor or within such further time as may be allowed; or`
  line
  line `(b) who fails to comply with the requirements of the chit agreement regarding the date, time and`
  line `place at which the chit is to be drawn or who fails to comply with the requirements of any direction`
  line `given under sub-section (3) of section 38; or`
  line
  line `(c) who contravenes or fails to comply with any other requirement under this Act,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction, be punishable with fine which may extend to three thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever wilfully makes a statement in any document required to be filed under this Act which is`
  line `false in any material particular shall, on conviction, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to two years or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (32153)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Penalty for second and subsequent convictions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32153&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `If any person convicted of an offence under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) of section 76 is again convicted of an offence under any of the said`
  line `sub-sections he shall be punishable for the second and for every subsequent offence with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to two years and shall also be liable to fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (32154)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Application of fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32154&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `A court imposing any fine under this Act may direct that the whole or any`
  line `part thereof shall be applied in, or towards payment of, the cost of the proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (32155)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32155&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer for the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (32156)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32156&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `(1) All offences under section 11 shall be cognizable.`
  line
  line `(2) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class`
  line `shall try an offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (32157)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Power to compound offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32157&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, any officer`
  line `empowered by the State Government in this behalf may, either before or after the institution of criminal`
  line `proceedings under this Act, accept from the person who has committed or is reasonably suspected to have`
  line `committed an offence under this Act, by way of composition of such offence, a sum of money not`
  line `exceeding such amount as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence has been compounded under sub-section (1), the offender, if in custody, shall be`
  line `discharged and no further proceedings shall be taken against him in respect of such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (32158)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Power to enter and search any place and to seize any documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32158&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Registrar or any`
  line `other officer authorised by him in this behalf, has reason to suspect that any person conducts, or is`
  line `responsible for the conduct of, a chit in any place in contravention of the provisions of this Act, he may,`
  line `for reasons to be recorded in writing and at any reasonable time, enter into and search such place, and`
  line `may seize such books, registers, accounts or documents as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar or officer authorised by him in this behalf, may apply for assistance to an officer in`
  line `charge of a police station and take police officers to accompany and assist him in discharging his duties`
  line `under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) All searches under sub-section (1) shall be made in accordance with the provisions of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (32159)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Officers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32159&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `The Registrar and all officers appointed by the State`
  line `Government to perform any functions under this Act shall be deemed to be public servants within the`
  line `meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (32160)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32160&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct`
  line `that any power (other than the power to hear appeals or to make rules) exercisable by it under this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder may be exercised also by any officer of the State Government subject to such`
  line `terms and conditions, if any, as may be specified therein.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line [Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 84.--In section 84 of the principal Act, the words “to hear appeals or” shall`
  line `be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 2 of 2008, s. 3.]`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (32161)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Act not to apply to certain chits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 2019, s. 9, for “one hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32161&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall apply in respect of`
  line
  line `(a) any chit started before the commencement of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) any chit the amount of which, or where two or more chits were started or conducted`
  line `simultaneously by the same foreman, the aggregate amount of which does not exceed ^1[such amount`
  line `as may be specified, by notification in the Official Gazette, by the State Goverment].`
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (32162)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Banks not to conduct chit business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32162&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no`
  line `bank shall commence or carry on chit business after the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a chit had been started by any bank before such commencement, such chit may be`
  line `continued after such commencement until it is completed, and the provisions of the chit agreement and`
  line `such laws, if any, as were applicable to it immediately before the commencement of this Act shall apply`
  line `to such chit.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section "bank" means an approved bank or a co-operative`
  line `bank as defined in clause (bii) of section 2 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934).`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (32163)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32163&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, and subject to such conditions as may be specified in the notification,`
  line `exempt any person or class of persons or any chit or class of chits from all or any of the provisions of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (32164)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Protection of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32164&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the State Government, the Registrar or other officers of the State Government or of the Reserve Bank or any of its officers exercising any powers or discharging any functions under this Act in respect of`
  line `anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or the rules made`
  line thereunder.
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (32165)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32165&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form and manner in which an application for obtaining the previous sanction may be made`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the additional particulars that a chit agreement may contain under clause (q) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the particulars that may be included in the minutes of the proceedings of a draw under`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(d) the method of valuation by the Registrar in a grain chit for the purpose of furnishing security`
  line `under section 20;`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure that may be followed by the Registrar in releasing the security furnished by the`
  line `foreman under section 20;`
  line
  line `(f) the registers and books and the form in which such registers and books may be maintained by`
  line `the foreman under section 23;`
  line
  line `(g) the time within which the balance sheet and the profit and loss account in respect of a chit`
  line `business shall be filed under section 24;`
  line
  line `(h) the rate at which interest shall be payable on the defaulted instalments by a defaulted`
  line `subscriber under section 28;`
  line
  line `(i) the particulars that may be included in an application for the winding up of chits under`
  line `section 49;`
  line
  line `(j) the procedure to be followed for the winding up of chits under Chapter X;`
  line
  line `(k) the fees payable under section 63;`
  line
  line `(l) the auditing of balance sheets and the profit and loss accounts of chit business and the issue of`
  line `audit certificates;`
  line
  line `(m) the form and manner in which a dispute shall be referred to the Registrar under section 64;`
  line
  line `(n) the procedure to be followed by the Registrar or his nominee for settling the disputes referred`
  line `to him under section 64;`
  line
  line `(o) the matters referred to in clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 67;`
  line
  line `(p) the conditions subject to which and the amount on the payment of which composition of`
  line `offences may be made under section 81;`
  line
  line `(q) the form and manner in which an appeal may be preferred under this Act and the fees payable`
  line `for such appeal;`
  line
  line `(r) the issue and service of notices or other process under this Act;`
  line
  line `(s) the procedure for, and the manner of, receiving any sum payable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(t) any other matter which is required to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made before each`
  line `House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or, where such Legislature consists of one`
  line `House before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (32166)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163&sectionId=32166&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00050_198240_1517807326163
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Andhra Pradesh Chit Funds Act, 1971 (Andhra Pradesh`
  line `Act 9 of 1971), the Kerala Chitties Act, 1975 (Kerala Act 23 of 1975), the Maharashtra Chit Funds`
  line `Act, 1974 (Maharashtra Act LV of 1974), the Tamil Nadu Chit Funds Act, 1961 (Tamil Nadu`
  line `Act 24 of 1961), as in force in the State of Tamil Nadu and in the Union territories of Chandigarh and`
  line `Delhi, the Uttar Pradesh Chit Funds Act, 1975 (Uttar Pradesh Act 53 of 1975), the Goa, Daman and Diu`
  line `Chit Funds Act, 1973 (Goa, Daman and Diu Act 16 of 1973) and the Pondicherry Chit Funds`
  line `Act, 1966 (Pondicherry Act 18 of 1966), are hereby repealed and the provisions of section 6 of the`
  line `General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), shall apply to such repeal as if each such Act so repealed were a`
  line `Central Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, the Acts mentioned in sub-section (1) shall continue to apply to chits`
  line `in operation on the commencement of this Act, in the same manner as they applied to such chits before`
  line `such commencement.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
